Within 3 months after the application for approval of reorganization is filed for examination, the Commissioner shall approve or reject the application. The Commissioner may not approve the application unless the Commissioner determines:
That the plan of reorganization is:
Reasonably required to protect the welfare of the general economy of this State;
Not detrimental to the public interest or the savings bank; and
In compliance with the regulations and conditions that the Commissioner adopts;
That if the reorganization is pursuant to an acquisition by the mutual holding company of all the stock of a savings and loan association:
Exigent circumstances exist that make the acquisition necessary to maintain the viability or prevent the probable failure of the savings and loan association acquired; and
The mutual holding company agrees to obtain federal insurance for the deposits of the acquired savings and loan association within the time limitation imposed by the Commissioner;
That immediately before the reorganization, the depositors of the savings bank are entitled to deposits in the subsidiary savings bank of like amounts, interest rates, and other terms, without interruption of interest;
That all deposits continue to be insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation up to the maximum amount provided by law; and
That the applicant has met all the requirements of this subtitle and Subtitle 9 of this title.
